adtranUnitMib.name: adtranUnitMib
adtranUnitMib.contactinfo: Technical Support Dept. Postal: ADTRAN, Inc. 901 Explorer Blvd. Huntsville, AL 35806 Tel: +1 800 726-8663 Fax: +1 256 963 6217 E-mail: support@adtran.com
adtranUnitMib.description: The MIB module for general unit configuration.

AdTftpConfigXferStatus.name: AdTftpConfigXferStatus
AdTftpConfigXferStatus.description: The status of a TFTP transfer

AdDualLEDstatus.name: AdDualLEDstatus
AdDualLEDstatus.description: The status of an individual LED which has more than one color.

adUnitDateTime.name: adUnitDateTime
adUnitDateTime.description: The current unit date and time.

adUnitMaxTelnetAccess.name: adUnitMaxTelnetAccess
adUnitMaxTelnetAccess.description: The maximum number of active telnet sessions.

adUnitEncryptPasswords.name: adUnitEncryptPasswords
adUnitEncryptPasswords.description: Determines whether or not the locally stored user passwords are encrypted.

adUnitEventLogging.name: adUnitEventLogging
adUnitEventLogging.description: Enable/Disable event logging on the unit.

adUnitClearEventLog.name: adUnitClearEventLog
adUnitClearEventLog.description: Set to 1 to clear all entries from unit's local event log.

adUnitRebootSystem.name: adUnitRebootSystem
adUnitRebootSystem.description: Set to 1 to initiate system reboot.

adUnitFactoryDefaultSystem.name: adUnitFactoryDefaultSystem
adUnitFactoryDefaultSystem.description: Set to 1 to set factory defaults configuration values for the entire unit.

adUnitSchedResetTime.name: adUnitSchedResetTime
adUnitSchedResetTime.description: Date and Time of scheduled system reset.

adUnitUserTable.name: adUnitUserTable
adUnitUserTable.description: A list of users who are allowed access to the unit.

adUnitUserEntry.name: adUnitUserEntry
adUnitUserEntry.description: Each entry in the list defines the user/pass, authen method, access level, and timeout.

adUnitUserIndex.name: adUnitUserIndex
adUnitUserIndex.description: Sequential index of the list of defined users.

adUnitUserAuthenMethod.name: adUnitUserAuthenMethod
adUnitUserAuthenMethod.description: The type of authentication to perform for this user.

adUnitUserIdleTime.name: adUnitUserIdleTime
adUnitUserIdleTime.description: The idle timeout value in minutes for a connection. If no operator activity is detected for this interval the connection is terminated. If the value is set to 0, the session will not be disconnected due to inactivity.

adUnitUserLevel.name: adUnitUserLevel
adUnitUserLevel.description: This is the level of access this user has.

adUnitUserIpAddr.name: adUnitUserIpAddr
adUnitUserIpAddr.description: If not null, the only IP address (or hostname) from which the specified user may initiate a telnet access.

adUnitUserState.name: adUnitUserState
adUnitUserState.description: Indication of whether or not the user has an active session.

adUnitUserStatus.name: adUnitUserStatus
adUnitUserStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the adUnitUserStatus column is 'notReady'.

adUnitSNMPCommunitiesTable.name: adUnitSNMPCommunitiesTable
adUnitSNMPCommunitiesTable.description: Contains a list of users who have SNMP access to this unit.

adUnitSNMPCommunitiesEntry.name: adUnitSNMPCommunitiesEntry
adUnitSNMPCommunitiesEntry.description: Each entry in the list defines the community string, access privilege, and Manager IP address.

adUnitSNMPCommunitiesString.name: adUnitSNMPCommunitiesString
adUnitSNMPCommunitiesString.description: The community string which has the specified SNMP access.

adUnitSNMPCommunitiesPrivilege.name: adUnitSNMPCommunitiesPrivilege
adUnitSNMPCommunitiesPrivilege.description: Set the SNMP privileges of this user.

adUnitSNMPCommunitiesMngmtIP.name: adUnitSNMPCommunitiesMngmtIP
adUnitSNMPCommunitiesMngmtIP.description: The IP address of the manager station. Set to '0.0.0.0' to enable the string for all addresses.

adUnitSNMPCommunitiesStatus.name: adUnitSNMPCommunitiesStatus
adUnitSNMPCommunitiesStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the adUnitSNMPCommunitiesStatus column is 'notReady'.

adUnitSNMPTrapsTable.name: adUnitSNMPTrapsTable
adUnitSNMPTrapsTable.description: Contains a list of users that will receive SNMP traps from this unit.

adUnitSNMPTrapsEntry.name: adUnitSNMPTrapsEntry
adUnitSNMPTrapsEntry.description: Each entry in the list defines the name, privilege, and Manager IP address.

adUnitSNMPTrapsString.name: adUnitSNMPTrapsString
adUnitSNMPTrapsString.description: The community string included in the SNMP traps.

adUnitSNMPTrapsMngmtAddr.name: adUnitSNMPTrapsMngmtAddr
adUnitSNMPTrapsMngmtAddr.description: The hostname (or IP address) that will receive SNMP traps.

adUnitSNMPTrapsStatus.name: adUnitSNMPTrapsStatus
adUnitSNMPTrapsStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the adUnitSNMPTrapsStatus column is 'notReady'.

adUnitSNMPEnableTraps.name: adUnitSNMPEnableTraps
adUnitSNMPEnableTraps.description: Enables or disables the transmission of all Traps.

adUnitSNMPAuthenticationTraps.name: adUnitSNMPAuthenticationTraps
adUnitSNMPAuthenticationTraps.description: Enables or disables the transmission of Authentication Traps.

adConsoleAccessMode.name: adConsoleAccessMode
adConsoleAccessMode.description: Specify operational mode of console. 0: No Authentication; no login required, CLI active automatically 1: Password Only 2: Username and password required

adConsoleLoginTimeout.name: adConsoleLoginTimeout
adConsoleLoginTimeout.description: Specifies the amount of time the system will wait for user input for a username &/or password before timing out and resetting back to intial prompt state. The time is specified in seconds. If the value is set to 0, the session will not be disconnected due to inactivity. Some units may implement a maximum allowable which is less than that specified.

adConsoleBaudRate.name: adConsoleBaudRate
adConsoleBaudRate.description: The baud rate for the console port.

adConsoleDataBits.name: adConsoleDataBits
adConsoleDataBits.description: The data bits for the console port.

adConsoleParity.name: adConsoleParity
adConsoleParity.description: The parity scheme for the console port.

adConsoleStopBits.name: adConsoleStopBits
adConsoleStopBits.description: The number of stop bits for the console port.

adConsoleFlowControl.name: adConsoleFlowControl
adConsoleFlowControl.description: The flow control mechanism for the console port. hardware control is via RTS/CTS and xOn/xOff is via transmission of the characters Control-S and Control-Q. Units may not support both control methods & hence may reject attempts to Set to ones not supported .

adConsoleModemInitString.name: adConsoleModemInitString
adConsoleModemInitString.description: Initialization string to send to connected modem.

adConsoleInitModem.name: adConsoleInitModem
adConsoleInitModem.description: Set value to 1 to force unit to attempt to initialize a connected modem on the console port by sending the contents of adConsoleModemInitString.

adUnitSyslogTransmission.name: adUnitSyslogTransmission
adUnitSyslogTransmission.description: Enables or disables the transmission of log events to the external Syslog server.

adUnitSyslogSrvrName.name: adUnitSyslogSrvrName
adUnitSyslogSrvrName.description: The Host IP Address specifies the hostname or IP address of the external server that is running the Syslog host daemon.

adUnitSyslogHostFacility.name: adUnitSyslogHostFacility
adUnitSyslogHostFacility.description: The Host Facility specifies the facility destination of log events. Facilities are located on the host and are managed by the Syslog host daemon running on either a UNIX machine or a PC.

adUnitSyslogMinSeverity.name: adUnitSyslogMinSeverity
adUnitSyslogMinSeverity.description: MinSeverity Level specifies the minimum level of severity that will cause messages to be logged to the Syslog server. The levels are listed in order of decreasing severity and any message at or above the selected severity level will be logged if transmission is enabled. 1. Emergency: system is unusable 2. Alert: action must be taken immediately 3. Critical: critical conditions 4. Error: error conditions 5. Warning: warning conditions 6. Notice: normal, but significant, conditions 7. Info: informational message 8. Debug: debug-level message

adUpdtFwXfrMethod.name: adUpdtFwXfrMethod
adUpdtFwXfrMethod.description: Method of downloading firmware to the unit.

adUpdtFwTFTPSrvAddr.name: adUpdtFwTFTPSrvAddr
adUpdtFwTFTPSrvAddr.description: The hostname or IP address of the TFTP server.

adUpdtFwXfrModule.name: adUpdtFwXfrModule
adUpdtFwXfrModule.description: The module (slot) to update with the Firmware transfer.

adUpdtFwXfrControl.name: adUpdtFwXfrControl
adUpdtFwXfrControl.description: Start the current firmware transfer by setting value to 1 and stop a transfer in progress by setting value to 0.

adUnitXferConfigMethod.name: adUnitXferConfigMethod
adUnitXferConfigMethod.description: Method to download/upload the unit's configuration.

adUnitConfigTFTPSrvAddr.name: adUnitConfigTFTPSrvAddr
adUnitConfigTFTPSrvAddr.description: Hostname or IP address of the TFTP server.

adUnitConfigTFTPSrvFileName.name: adUnitConfigTFTPSrvFileName
adUnitConfigTFTPSrvFileName.description: The filename to download/upload from the TFTP server.

adUnitConfigCurrXfrStatus.name: adUnitConfigCurrXfrStatus
adUnitConfigCurrXfrStatus.description: The status of the current configuration file transfer.

adUnitConfigPrevXfrStatus.name: adUnitConfigPrevXfrStatus
adUnitConfigPrevXfrStatus.description: The status of the previous the configuration file transfer.

adUpdtConfigXfrModule.name: adUpdtConfigXfrModule
adUpdtConfigXfrModule.description: If 0 through 35 is selected, the source or destination module (slot) for the configuration transfer. If -1 is selected the entire configuration is transfered.

adUnitXferConfig.name: adUnitXferConfig
adUnitXferConfig.description: Set value to 1 to transfer the configuration file from the tftp server and switch to the configuration. Set value to 2 to transfer the configuration file to the tftp server.

adUnitCurrentCpuUtil.name: adUnitCurrentCpuUtil
adUnitCurrentCpuUtil.description: Average CPU utilization over the last second.

adUnitTotalCpuUtil.name: adUnitTotalCpuUtil
adUnitTotalCpuUtil.description: Average CPU utilization since last system reboot or statistics reset.

adUnitClearUtilizationStats.name: adUnitClearUtilizationStats
adUnitClearUtilizationStats.description: Set value to 1 to clear CPU utilization statistics.

adUnitPingStatus.name: adUnitPingStatus
adUnitPingStatus.description: Set value to 1 to Stop ping sequence and 2 to start ping sequence.

adUnitPingMode.name: adUnitPingMode
adUnitPingMode.description: Set the 'sweep' BIT to cause the ping process to send consecutively increasing buffer sizes starting at adUnitPingPktMinSize and continueing to adUnitPingPktMaxSize. If 'sweep' is not set, a single packet size of adUnitPingPktMinSize is used. The default is for sweep to not be set. Set the 'verbose' bit for responses to be reported via entries in the adUnitPingRespTbl. If 'verbose' is not set, results are reported via adUnitPingResult. The default is for verbose to not be set.

adUnitPingTarget.name: adUnitPingTarget
adUnitPingTarget.description: Host name or IP Address of the unit to ping.

adUnitPingPktMinSize.name: adUnitPingPktMinSize
adUnitPingPktMinSize.description: If in normal mode specifies the size of the ping request buffer. In Sweep mode the mininum initial size.

adUnitPingPktMaxSize.name: adUnitPingPktMaxSize
adUnitPingPktMaxSize.description: Not used in normal mode. In Sweep mode, the maximum buffer size used for the sweep. If the value is not greater than adUnitPingPktMinSize the sweep will terminate after the first buffer size completes.

adUnitPingFillBuffer.name: adUnitPingFillBuffer
adUnitPingFillBuffer.description: Specify the characters to replicate within the outgoing request buffer.

adUnitPingSource.name: adUnitPingSource
adUnitPingSource.description: The IP Address to be inserted into source field of transmitted message. If set to the default of 0.0.0.0, the address of the source network interface ( determined from the route table) is used.

adUnitPingTimeout.name: adUnitPingTimeout
adUnitPingTimeout.description: Specify the Timeout for each ping request, specified in seconds.

adUnitPingRepeatCnt.name: adUnitPingRepeatCnt
adUnitPingRepeatCnt.description: Specify the number of times to repeat the ping request. For verbose mode maximum allowed is 50, for normal mode, the maximum is 255.

adUnitPingXmtNum.name: adUnitPingXmtNum
adUnitPingXmtNum.description: The actual number of ping requests transmitted.

adUnitPingResult.name: adUnitPingResult
adUnitPingResult.description: Output string to show results of ping when in normal mode. If more than 255 transmissions are generated during the ping execution only the results of the first 255 are reported. The following characters indicate the specified results: ! OK . Timeout, no response U Destination Unreachable Q Source Quench (destination too busy) M Could not fragment ? Unknown Packet type & Packet lifetime exceeded

adUnitPingMinRndTrp.name: adUnitPingMinRndTrp
adUnitPingMinRndTrp.description: The minimum round-trip time in milliseconds.

adUnitPingMaxRndTrp.name: adUnitPingMaxRndTrp
adUnitPingMaxRndTrp.description: The maximum round-trip time in milliseconds.

adUnitPingAvgRndTrp.name: adUnitPingAvgRndTrp
adUnitPingAvgRndTrp.description: The average round-trip time in milliseconds.

adUnitPingVerboseTable.name: adUnitPingVerboseTable
adUnitPingVerboseTable.description: A table reporting the verbose output of the last ping test initiated via SNMP.

adUnitPingVerboseEntry.name: adUnitPingVerboseEntry
adUnitPingVerboseEntry.description: Each entry in the list is the result of a single ping request. Each request is identified by its sequence number, adPingRespIndex.

adPingRespStatus.name: adPingRespStatus
adPingRespStatus.description: The compeletion status of the ping response: 1 - OK 2 - Target address is unknown 3 - Invalid Source address 4 - No response received before timeout expired 5 - Unreachable destination (adPingRespAddr contains reporting address) 6 - TTL expired in transit (adPingRespAddr contains reporting address)

adPingRespTime.name: adPingRespTime
adPingRespTime.description: Time in milliseconds to receive response.

adPingRespTTL.name: adPingRespTTL
adPingRespTTL.description: TTL value of the response. For TTL to be reported, the buffer size of the request (adUnitPingPktSize) must be at least 4 bytes.

adUnitTraceRtStatus.name: adUnitTraceRtStatus
adUnitTraceRtStatus.description: Set value to 0 to interrupt and stop a TraceRoute sequence and 1 to start a TraceRoute sequence. When TraceRoute completes value with change from 'active' to 'inActive'.

adUnitTraceRtTarget.name: adUnitTraceRtTarget
adUnitTraceRtTarget.description: Host name or IP Address of the unit to probe.

adUnitTraceRtSource.name: adUnitTraceRtSource
adUnitTraceRtSource.description: The IP Address to be inserted into source field of transmitted message. If set to the default of 0.0.0.0, the unit address is used.

adUnitTraceRtTimeout.name: adUnitTraceRtTimeout
adUnitTraceRtTimeout.description: The response timeout for all traceroute probes.

adUnitTraceRtProbeCnt.name: adUnitTraceRtProbeCnt
adUnitTraceRtProbeCnt.description: The number of probes to initiate for each TTL.

adUnitTraceRtMinTTL.name: adUnitTraceRtMinTTL
adUnitTraceRtMinTTL.description: The Minimum Time To Live value (hops) of the traceroute probes.

adUnitTraceRtMaxTTL.name: adUnitTraceRtMaxTTL
adUnitTraceRtMaxTTL.description: Specify the Maximum Time To Live value (hops) of the traceroute probes.

adUnitTraceRtPortNum.name: adUnitTraceRtPortNum
adUnitTraceRtPortNum.description: Set the base UDP port number used in probes. Traceroute operation is based on the fact that nothing is listening on UDP ports base to base + nhops - 1 at the destination host (so an ICMP PORT_UNREACHABLE message will be returned to terminate the route tracing). If something is listening on a port in the default range, this option can be used to pick an unused port range.

adUnitTraceRtRespTable.name: adUnitTraceRtRespTable
adUnitTraceRtRespTable.description: A table reporting the output of each traceroute probe initiated via SNMP. Upon initiation of a traceroute any existing entries in the table are automatically deleted by the agent & new records are inserted to reflect the results of the most recent traceroute test.

adUnitTraceRtRespEntry.name: adUnitTraceRtRespEntry
adUnitTraceRtRespEntry.description: Each entry in the list is the result of a single probe request intiated by traceroute. Each request is identified by its TTL number, adTraceRtRespIndex. When a trace route is started all entries are deleted from the table and then inserted as the result of each attempt is determined

adTraceRtRespString.name: adTraceRtRespString
adTraceRtRespString.description: The response output from the traceroute process for each probe.

adUnitFaceplate.name: adUnitFaceplate
adUnitFaceplate.description: A bit encoded string representing the status of all faceplate indicators, LEDs, & switches for GUI visualization of the unit. Each product defines this as a bitmap of booleans, or a byte for each indicator if not binary. The strings from all the slots are concatenated into this one object, after prefixing each card indicator string with two bytes. The first byte contains the slot number as an integer, and the second byte contains the remaining string length for that slot. The Textual Convention AdDualLEDstatus should be used for non-binary states.

adUnitAlarmStatus.name: adUnitAlarmStatus
adUnitAlarmStatus.description: A bit encoded string representing a summary of the alarm state of the chassis. Refer to individual unit documentation for the specification of the bimask

adUnitSlotInfoTable.name: adUnitSlotInfoTable
adUnitSlotInfoTable.description: Table of slots available for boards.

adUnitSlotInfoEntry.name: adUnitSlotInfoEntry
adUnitSlotInfoEntry.description: General information descibing the contents of each card slot.

adUnitSlotInfoIndex.name: adUnitSlotInfoIndex
adUnitSlotInfoIndex.description: A unique value for each slot. Its value may exceed the value of adUnitSlotNumber if pseudo slot numbers are used for some bank commons or multiplexers.

adUnitSlotProdSwVersion.name: adUnitSlotProdSwVersion
adUnitSlotProdSwVersion.description: The Adtran Product Software Version Number.

adUnitSlotProdPhysAddress.name: adUnitSlotProdPhysAddress
adUnitSlotProdPhysAddress.description: This octet string variable contains the Adtran Physical Address assigned to this product. For example the octet sequence, 16 02 03 01, specifies channel bank number 16, digroup number 2, DS0 channel slot number 3, position 1. This object value is commonly reported in SNMP Traps to identify the product's location.

adUnitSlotInfoState.name: adUnitSlotInfoState
adUnitSlotInfoState.description: The state of the card slot. Initially it is empty. When a card is inserted, it becomes occupied, and the Slot Type is determined by the card Product Code. When a card is removed, it changes to virtual, and retains the SlotType characteristics until a different kind of card is inserted, or a different preconfiguration is established.

adUnitSlotProduct.name: adUnitSlotProduct
adUnitSlotProduct.description: The ADTRAN Product code, 0 if empty. Agent will report real product code when installed or pre-provisioned.

adUnitSlotTrapEnable.name: adUnitSlotTrapEnable
adUnitSlotTrapEnable.description: Enables/Disables traps initiated from this slot.

adUnitSlotAlarmStatus.name: adUnitSlotAlarmStatus
adUnitSlotAlarmStatus.description: A bit encoded string representing the alarm state of the slot. The LSB should be 1 for No Alarm, else 0 and the higher order bits will indicate which alarms are present. The specific alarm conditions may be found in more specific generic MIBs or in the device MIB.

adUnitSlotFaceplate.name: adUnitSlotFaceplate
adUnitSlotFaceplate.description: A bit encoded string representing the status of faceplate indicators, LEDs, & switches for GUI visualization associated with the card in the respective slot. Each product defines this as a bitmap of booleans, or a byte for each indicator if not binary. The Textual Convention AdDualLEDstatus should be used for non-binary states.

adUnitSlotServiceState.name: adUnitSlotServiceState
adUnitSlotServiceState.description: Module service state. The full enumeration is supported by CND products. END products may support only the following subset with the END equivalent state following '/': is -- InService / Online oosUas -- Out of Service, Unasssigned / Unavailable oosMA -- Out of Sevice, Maint. / Offline

adUnitPortInfoTable.name: adUnitPortInfoTable
adUnitPortInfoTable.description: A table of hardware oriented port information on each card. This only includes actual card ports, and not layered logical interfaces.

adUnitPortInfoEntry.name: adUnitPortInfoEntry
adUnitPortInfoEntry.description: A row table entry exists for each card/port pair.

adUnitPortInfoIndex.name: adUnitPortInfoIndex
adUnitPortInfoIndex.description: A unique value for each physical port on a card.

adUnitPortInfoState.name: adUnitPortInfoState
adUnitPortInfoState.description: The state of the card port. Initially it is empty.

adUnitPortIfIndex.name: adUnitPortIfIndex
adUnitPortIfIndex.description: The interface number identified as ifIndex from the MIB-II interfaces table as defined by the slot and port numbers in this device.

adUnitPortAlarmStatus.name: adUnitPortAlarmStatus
adUnitPortAlarmStatus.description: A bit encoded string representing the alarm state of the port.

adUnitPortDescription.name: adUnitPortDescription
adUnitPortDescription.description: A character string to identify the name of a port. Used for trap varbind in last trap sent. Should default to port number string. Can be overridden by customer as desired.

adUnitPortSlotMapTable.name: adUnitPortSlotMapTable
adUnitPortSlotMapTable.description: Table to map ifIndex to slot, port & type.

adUnitPortSlotMapEntry.name: adUnitPortSlotMapEntry
adUnitPortSlotMapEntry.description: An entry exists for each interface which is mapped to a physical slot/port pair.

adUnitSlotAddress.name: adUnitSlotAddress
adUnitSlotAddress.description: The slot in which this port is contained. Slot 0 is reported for the unit controller and all logical interfaces.

adUnitPortAddress.name: adUnitPortAddress
adUnitPortAddress.description: The port number within the slot. Logical interfaces should indicate port 0.

adUnitCompliance.name: adUnitCompliance
adUnitCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities which implement the adUnit MIB.

adUnitsCndGroup.name: adUnitsCndGroup
adUnitsCndGroup.description: The CND Management Group. Support for this group is only required when the unit is to be managed in a CND environment. For instance, IADs which are remotely provisioned by a service provider via Total Access EMS.

adUnitsExtendedBaseGroup.name: adUnitsExtendedBaseGroup
adUnitsExtendedBaseGroup.description: The Extended Base Group containing functions not supported by all units.

adUnitsExtendedSNMPGroup.name: adUnitsExtendedSNMPGroup
adUnitsExtendedSNMPGroup.description: The Extended SNMP Group containing functions not supported by all units.

adConsoleModemGroup.name: adConsoleModemGroup
adConsoleModemGroup.description: The Console Modem Group containing functions not supported by all units.

adUnitsExtendedSyslogGroup.name: adUnitsExtendedSyslogGroup
adUnitsExtendedSyslogGroup.description: The Extended Syslog Group containing functions not supported by all units.

adUnitExtendedPingGroup.name: adUnitExtendedPingGroup
adUnitExtendedPingGroup.description: The Unit Ping Group supporting extended Ping operations (for instance, sweep & verbose modes).
